description: Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez said Friday he will on Wednesday announce the date on which Madrid will recognize a Palestinian state along with other nations.
title: Spain to recognize Palestinian state together with other countries

description: Israel’s military said around 75 rockets were fired at northern Israel from Lebanese territory.
title: 75 rockets fired at northern Israel

description: The Palestinian Red Crescent Society (PRCS) said on Thursday that 15,103 children have been killed since the start of the Israeli brutal war on the Gaza Strip on October 7.
title: Red Crescent: 15,000 children have been killed in Gaza

description: TEHRAN – The Commander of the Iranian Army Ground Forces says the country will respond directly to any threats originating from the Zionist regime.
title: Any threat will receive direct response: commander

description: TEHRAN— The Spokesperson and Additional Foreign Secretary of Pakistan has emphasized the enduring brotherly relations between Tehran and Islamabad, reiterating Pakistan's strong commitment to enhancing cooperation between Chabahar and Gwadar Ports.
title: Pakistan advocates strengthening partnership between Chabahar, Gwadar ports

description:
* Paintings by Elham Heidari are on display in an exhibition at Doost Gallery.
Entitled “Flowing Nature”, the exhibit will be running until June 2 at the gallery, which can be found at No. 4, 4th St. off Eshqyar St., Khorramshahr Ave.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of “The Book of Gaza: A City in Short Fiction” edited by the Palestinian writer Atef Abu Saif has been released during the 35th Tehran International Book Fair, which is underway in Tehran, from May 8 to 18.
title: Persian translation of “The Book of Gaza” released at 35th TIBF

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian short film “Cocoon” written and directed by Saeid Bojnourdi has won an award at the 15th Annual World Music and Independent Film Festival in Virginia, the U.S.
title: Iranian actor Milad Shajareh wins at American festival

description: TEHRAN-Iranian actress Zahra Khoshkam passed away on Thursday night in Tehran at the age of 77.
title: Zahra Khoshkam passes away at 77

description: TEHRAN- A group of Iranian calligraphers has come together to protest Israeli atrocities against Palestinians through a unique form of artistic expression, writing the Al-Fil Surah in solidarity with the Palestinian cause on the sidelines of "Narration of Rain" Quranic art exhibition.
title: Iranian calligraphers unite to protest Israeli atrocities

description: TEHRAN - The commander of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) Quds Force, Brigadier General Esmail Qaani, has declared that the three European countries that deployed warplanes to defend Israel during Iran's retaliatory "True Promise" Operation will be held accountable.
title: European trio will face accountability for aid to Israel during Iran’s retaliation: Commander

description: TEHRAN- A newly appointed Sociocultural advisor to President Ebrahim Raisi has asserted that increased access to virtual platforms has exposed the realities of Israel and its allies, suggesting that the global uprising spurred by Zionist actions will expedite the fall of Tel Aviv.
title: Global uprising for Gaza hastens Zionists' demise: advisor

description: TEHRAN— The Chief of Iran’s Army, Major General Abdolrahim Mousavi, has declared that the Islamic Republic’s retaliatory response to the Zionist regime, known as Operation True Promise, will hasten the liberation of Palestine and the downfall of the Zionist regime.
title: Army chief asserts Opt. True Promise accelerates Palestine’s liberation

description: Yemen’s army says it has shot down an American spy drone by “a locally-made missile” in the province of Ma’rib, amid escalating tensions in the region over Israel’s US-backed genocidal war on the Gaza Strip.
title: Yemen downs advanced $30 million US spy drone

description: TEHRAN— The Republic of Azerbaijan’s foreign ministry spokesperson, Ayhan Hajizadeh, has announced that a new location for the country’s embassy in Tehran has been determined.
title: Azerbaijan announces new location for embassy in Iran

description: TEHRAN – Iran's permanent representative to the United Nations has forcefully rebutted recent accusations by the United States about the Islamic Republic’s interference in Yemen.
title: Iran rejects allegations of interference in Yemen, calls U.S. claims ‘short-sighted’

description: TEHRAN – The White House is caught between a rock and a hard place as it continues to receive criticism from both the public and the Israeli lobby in the U.S. for its handling of the war in Gaza.
title: Jeffery Sachs: “U.S. complicit in Israeli war crimes”

description: TEHRAN- On May 12, the Israeli military announced 50 Israeli army casualties in Gaza – without distinguishing between the injured and the dead – the single highest casualty rate in a 24-hour time-frame inside the Strip since October 7.
title: Did “friendly fire” kill Israeli soldiers?

description: TEHRAN - Ali Baqeri Kani, the Iranian deputy foreign minister for political affairs, has highlighted the significance of the BRICS group as the primary nucleus and driving force of international collective will to establish a just world and safeguard the interests of independent nations.
title: BRICS first step towards a more just world: Iranian diplomat

description: TEHRAN - Israel used its notorious propaganda machine at the International Court of Justice (ICJ) by citing the most outrageous lies in an attempt to distract global attention away from the atrocious crimes that it has been committing in the Gaza Strip since October 7.
title: Transparent lies

description: A group of prominent American Jewish billionaires and business leaders have been privately pressuring New York City Mayor, Eric Adams, to deploy the police against pro-Palestinian student protesters at Columbia University, and even offered to pay for private investigators to assist the New York Police Department in handling the protests, according to a report by The Washington Post.
title: Pro-Israel billionaires caught plotting to crackdown student protests: Washington Post

description: TEHRAN - The third phase of the comprehensive restoration of the historical Aveh Caravanserai has commenced, according to the deputy tourism chief of Markazi province.
title: Restoration of 17th-century Aveh caravanserai enters 3rd phase

description: TEHRAN – On Wednesday, North Khorasan played host to a lively event, dedicated to bird-watching in the days in which the provincial wetlands welcomed special winged visitors.
title: Special guests of North Khorasan delight birders

description: TEHRAN – The 13th edition of a biennial conference on the conservation and restoration of historical-cultural relics and architectural elements will be held at Tabriz Islamic Art University on May 19 and 20.
title: Tabriz to host conference on historical property conservation

description: TEHRAN – Some of the world’s oldest tabletop games are arranged to be showcased in Iran’s Sistan-Baluchestan province in part of programs to celebrate National Cultural Heritage Week and International Museum Day.
title: Whispers of antiquity: Sistan-Baluchestan to unveil ancient tabletop games

description: TEHRAN - The millennia-old Gold Bowl of Hasanlu, a significant archaeological find named after the location where it was excavated some 66 years ago, will be showcased at the Urmia Museum of Archaeology in celebration of Cultural Heritage Week.
title: Gold Bowl of Hasanlu to go on view at Urmia Museum

description: Israeli Knesset member, Amit Halevi, confirmed on Thursday that all 24 Hamas brigades are still present in Gaza and not a single one of them has been destroyed, adding that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is lying to the Israeli people and inflating the army’s achievements, according to Middle East Monitor.
title: Israel MK: None of Hamas’ 24 brigades have been destroyed

description: Anyone listening to EU officials speak about Gaza would think that the only problem that the enclave is facing is a disruption in the distribution of humanitarian aid. International law, however, describes what is happening in Gaza very clearly – genocide – so why can’t the EU High Representative Josep Borrell be clear on what the bloc should be speaking out against and acting to prevent?
title: Diplomatic fatigue and heavy strain, but what about the genocide?

description: Prominent Israeli academic Ilan Pappe said he was interrogated by the Department of Homeland Security after arriving in the US on Monday, Middle East Eye reported on Friday.
title: Anti-Zionist academic interrogated by federal agents on Gaza views

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and his Chinese counterpart, Xi Jinping, have signed a joint statement on deepening the comprehensive strategic partnership between their two nations at a summit that framed their relationship as a stabilizing force in a chaotic world.
title: ‘Old friend’ Putin and China’s Xi strengthen strategic ties at summit

description: TEHRAN –Out of the 1036 vertebrate animal species of the country, around 75 are on the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) Red List, according to an official with the Department of Environment (DOE).
title: Some 75 animal species in Iran on IUCN Red List

description: TEHRAN –The Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) and the International Committee for Red Cross (ICRC) in Iran are conducting joint programs to address the challenges facing Afghan refugees and vulnerable Iranians residing in Golshahr district in Mashhad, northeastern Khorasan Razavi province.
title: IRCS, ICRC join hands to support Afghan refugees

description: TEHRAN – The Times Higher Education has placed Iran second among Islamic countries in terms of the number of universities included in Young University Rankings 2024.
title: Iran second among Islamic countries in Young University Rankings 2024

description: TEHRAN - Officials from Iran and Qatar emphasized the need for expanding cooperation in the field of aviation.
title: Tehran, Doha to expand aviation cooperation

description: TEHRAN – During a visit to the northern province of Mazandaran on Thursday, President Ebrahim Raisi inaugurated four major port development projects with a total investment of 2.55 trillion rials ($5.1 million) in Amirabad Port.
title: Raisi inaugurates development projects worth $5.1m in Mazandaran

description: TEHRAN - Negotiations are ongoing between Iran and Afghanistan for sidelining US dollar in bilateral transactions.
title: Tehran, Kabul to ditch US dollar in bilateral trade

description: TEHRAN – Iranian firms have signed 21 contracts valued at $2.75 billion to develop sea-based technologies during the 1st edition of Iran Sea-Based Economy International Matchmaking Event (ISBE 2024) in Qeshm Island, southern Iran
title: Deals worth $2.75b signed for developing sea-based economy

description: TEHRAN - The trade between the Islamic Republic of Iran and its neighbors has reached over $90 billion, Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amirabdollahian says.
title: Iran's trade with neighbors exceeds $90 billion: FM

description: TEHRAN - The head of the Railways of the Islamic Republic of Iran (RAI) said a $500 million fund has been allocated for purchasing the equipment, repairing and modernizing the railway fleet of the country using oil bartering.
title: RAI earmarks $500m for renovating railway fleet

description: TEHRAN - The head of Iran’s Power Generation, Distribution and Transmission Company (TAVANIR) has emphasized the country’s resolve to develop electricity trade with Turkey.
title: ‘Iran determined to expand electricity ties with Turkey’

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Ambassador to Russia Kazem Jalali has said the country is going to host a trilateral customs and transportation meeting with Russia and Azerbaijan.
title: Iran to host trilateral customs, transportation event with Russia, Azerbaijan
